Job Title:     Sr Consultant - Documentum
Job Location:  PA: Collegeville
Pay Rate:      competitive
Job Length:    full time
Start Date:    2007-08-14

Company Name:  Wyeth
Contact:       Wyeth
Phone:         email only
Fax:           email only

Description:   At Wyeth, we have a vision of leading the way to a healthier world. Weve committed ourselves to achieving this vision by making quality, integrity and excellence the hallmarks of our business. A Fortune 500 company and global leader in pharmaceuticals, consumer healthcare, and animal healthcare products, we know that our employees are who keep us on the cutting edge of innovative discoveries and superior customer service. To sustain and enhance our leadership position in the pharmaceutical industry, we continue to recruit, develop and motivate individuals whose skills, values, and work ethic will grow and improve our business.

Position is responsible for delivering Documentum based business solutions to client groups. Position drives the use of Documentum based systems within Wyeth by providing consulting expertise to a business unit (s) in the appropriate use and implementation of these solutions within their line of business. This person is the point person for information management organizations and other client stakeholders.  Works with the business unit to understand and map current and proposed business processes, identify and define technology initiatives that will support short- and long-term business objectives and strategies, complete analysis necessary to prioritize initiatives, including documentation of high level requirements, solution identification, budget and resource estimation, and cost-benefit analysis.

JOB ACCOUNTABILITIES - Uses advanced knowledge of software (specifically EMC Documentum product suite) and applies extensive expertise across technical areas to facilitate major cross-functional projects. Leads and recommends integrated cross process design decisions. Participates in process discussions and recommends resolution of design decisions to support functional initiatives.

Ensures business requirements are prioritized and delivery dates are agreed upon.  Evaluates the portfolio of projects and requests from a given client area.

Leverages advanced application knowledge in multiple enterprise technologies in evaluating the need and recommend the use of Documentum and/or other Enterprise Solution(s).  Manage/coordinate sophisticated project management across IS matrix for implementation.  Services to include:  Detailed Business Requirements, Business Process Mapping and Business Improvement Recommendations.

BASIC QUALIFICATION BS/BA or MS/MA + 12 years experience or a PhD and 6-7 years of experience in a Technical or Business field.

In depth familiarity with Documentums capabilities and limitations highly desired.  Familiarity with other Enterprise Solutions a plus.

Excellent communication and business process skills are required.  Familiarity with regulatory and proprietary information a plus.  Must be able to work in a collaborative team environment.

Documentum Compliance Manager (highly recommended)

2 -- 3 years of project management experience (recommended)

3 - 4 years of pharmaceutical industry experience (recommended)

Wyeth offers competitive compensation and benefits programs, including child-care subsidies, flex-time, business casual attire, educational assistance and professional development programs.

For more information and to apply online, please visit us at: www.wyeth.com/careers

